{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e7962be1-d692-4f8b-ac23-a26cadc1e27e","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your crash dump. The `dump-collect` skill I have available is only for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them — so let me give you the key approaches directly.\n\n## Analyzing a .NET Crash Dump\n\n**Option 1: `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform, recommended)\n```bash\n# Install the tool\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Open the dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `pe` | Print last exception |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary |\n| `setthread <id>` then `clrstack` | Inspect other threads |\n\nStart with `pe` (print exception) — it usually reveals the crash cause immediately.\n\n**Option 2: Visual Studio** (Windows)\n- Open the `.dmp` file directly → click **\"Debug with Managed Only\"**\n\n**Option 3: `lldb` with SOS** (Linux/macOS)\n```bash\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\n```\n\nWould you like help installing any of these tools or walking through specific analysis steps?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2520a35c-44ff-4421-bde8-c3b9a95399a3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the skill is not appropriate here. I should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":428,"requestId":"9810:10A2F9:D71B11:FB9344:69F407FD"},"id":"0358237e-db2a-47e0-8c7e-670304f099cb","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:55:20.946Z","parentId":"344424fc-3383-436d-9d2a-0617eee4d58c"}
